## Overview

For this project, I made a Python app that tracks sleep for multiple people. The idea was to have something where you can put in when someone goes to sleep and wakes up, and then actually see how much sleep they’re getting over time.

I didn’t want it to just run in the terminal, so I built a full interface for it. The program also calculates average sleep and graphs everything so it’s easier to understand.

---

## Project Goals

The goal of this project is to create an interactive application that allows multiple users to track and analyze their sleep patterns over time. Specifically, we aimed to:

- Build a graphical user interface (GUI) using Tkinter
- Allow users to input sleep and wake times across multiple days
- Store and manage data for multiple individuals
- Calculate total and average sleep duration
- Visualize sleep trends using graphs

## Tools I Used

I used Python for everything. Tkinter was used to build the interface, and Matplotlib was used to create the graphs. I also used GitHub to keep track of my code and changes while working on it.

